com.nokia.maps.routing.enums

Interface RouteLinkFlag

  • All Superinterfaces:
    RouteFeature

    public interface RouteLinkFlag
extends RouteFeature
    This Interface defines a series of constants for different link flags.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static java.lang.String FOUR_WHEEL_DRIVE
      This constant indicates a link is part of a road that is suitable only for vehicles with four-wheel drive.
      static java.lang.String GATED_AREA
      This constant indicates a link is part of a gated area.
      static java.lang.String NO_THROUGH_ROAD
      This constant indicates a link is part of a road that you can enter but you have to exit the same way.
      static java.lang.String PRIVATE_ROAD
      This constant indicates a link is part of a private road.
      static java.lang.String SCENIC
      This constant indicates a link that part of a road that has been marked as scenic.
      static java.lang.String STATION
      This constant indicates a link is located at a station.
      static java.lang.String UNKNOWN
      This constant indicates an "unknown" value.
      static java.lang.String UNPAVED
      This constant indicates a link is part of an unpaved road.

      • UNKNOWN

        static final java.lang.String UNKNOWN
        This constant indicates an "unknown" value. This indicates on client side that the backend has sent a new enumeration value which hasn't been defined when implementing the client. As the addition of new enumeration values in response types is defined as a backward compatible change on server side the client must be flexible enough to not break when facing new values.
